cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on improving generalization to low-resourced languages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of continuous word representations, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a method that does not require parallel corpora or bilingual dictionaries, which could fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with Named Entity Recognition (NER) and Machine Translation, which could fall under the categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
